"Cibois A., Thibault J.-C., Pasquet E.","Influence of quaternary sea-level variations on a land bird endemic to Pacific atolls",2010,"Proceedings of the Royal Society B: Biological Sciences","277","1699",,"3445","3451",,,10.1098/rspb.2010.0846,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78149233153&partnerID=40&md5=1b3299bd9737fefe6e26161ddfe33210","Department of Mammalogy and Ornithology, Natural History Museum of Geneva, CP 6434, 1211 Geneva 6, Switzerland; Département Systématique et Evolution, Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Structure et Evolution de la Biodiversité, 55 rue Buffon, Paris, France; Service de Systématique Moléculaire, UMS2700-CNRS, 43 rue Cuvier, 75005 Paris, France","Cibois, A., Department of Mammalogy and Ornithology, Natural History Museum of Geneva, CP 6434, 1211 Geneva 6, Switzerland; Thibault, J.-C., Département Systématique et Evolution, Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Structure et Evolution de la Biodiversité, 55 rue Buffon, Paris, France, Service de Systématique Moléculaire, UMS2700-CNRS, 43 rue Cuvier, 75005 Paris, France; Pasquet, E., Département Systématique et Evolution, Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Structure et Evolution de la Biodiversité, 55 rue Buffon, Paris, France, Service de Systématique Moléculaire, UMS2700-CNRS, 43 rue Cuvier, 75005 Paris, France","Little is known about the effect of quaternary climate variations on organisms that inhabited carbonate islands of the Pacific Ocean, although it has been suggested that one or several uplifted islands provided shelter for terrestrial birds when sea-level reached its highest. To test this hypothesis, we investigated the history of colonization of the Tuamotu reed-warbler (Acrocephalus atyphus) in southeastern Polynesia, and found high genetic structure between the populations of three elevated carbonate islands. Estimates of time since divergence support the hypothesis that these islands acted as refugia during the last interglacial maximum. These findings are particularly important for defining conservation priorities on atolls that endure the current trend of sea-level rise owing to global warming. © 2010 The Royal Society.","Atolls; Phylogeography; Reed-warblers; Refugia; Sea-level variations","microsatellite DNA; mitochondrial DNA; atoll; carbonate; colonization; endemic species; genetic structure; global warming; hypothesis testing; Last Interglacial; passerine; phylogeography; refuge; sea level change; animal; article; ecosystem; evolution; genetics; greenhouse effect; Pacific islands; physiology; population density; sea; songbird; Animals; Biological Evolution; DNA, Mitochondrial; Ecosystem; Global Warming; Microsatellite Repeats; Oceans and Seas; Pacific Islands; Passeriformes; Population Density; Pacific Ocean; Polynesia; Acrocephalus; Acrocephalus atyphus; Aves",,"DNA, Mitochondrial",,,,"Arnaud-Haond, S., Bonhomme, F., Blanc, F., Large discrepancies in differentiation of allozymes, nuclear and mitochondrial DNA loci in recently founded Pacific populations of the pearl oyster Pinctada margaritifera (2003) Journal of Evolutionary Biology, 16 (3), pp. 388-398. , DOI 10.1046/j.1420-9101.2003.00549.x; Bensch, S., Hasselquist, D., Phylogenetic population structure of great reed warblers: An analysis of mtDNA control region sequences (1999) Biol.J.Linn.Soc., (66), pp. 171-185. , doi:10.1111/j.1095-8312.1999.tb01882.x; Camoin, G.F., Ebren, Ph., Eisenhauer, A., Bard, E., Faure, G., A 300 000-yr coral reef record of sea level changes, Mururoa atoll (Tuamotu archipelago, French Polynesia) (2001) Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology, 175 (1-4), pp. 325-341. , DOI 10.1016/S0031-0182(01)00378-9, PII S0031018201003789; Chapuis, M.-P., Estoup, A., Microsatellite null alleles and estimation of population differentiation (2007) Molecular Biology and Evolution, 24 (3), pp. 621-631. , DOI 10.1093/molbev/msl191; Church, J.A., White, N.J., (2006) A 20th century acceleration in global sea-level rise.Geophys.Res.Le